    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - High-pressure Oil System - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s26511.4">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc id="s26511.4.2" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="7">
            <title>High-pressure Oil Pump and Branch Tube Assembly</title>
            <figure id="f3900006" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figN11/N11015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>High-pressure oil pump and branch tube</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Branch tube adaptor</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 30 bolt (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 45 bolt (3)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure oil pump</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring seal (pump inlet)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring seal (branch tube)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Branch tube assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 40 bolt (2)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not drop bolts into crankcase. Bolts are not captured within the
                        branch tube or oil pump.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install branch tube assembly into crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two M6 x 40 branch tube mounting bolts through the right and left sides of the
                    branch tube assembly and finger tighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001212" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figN11/N11018.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Branch tube adapter</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Jam nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Seal ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate jam nut to the base of the branch tube adaptor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new branch tube adaptor O-ring and lubricate with clean engine oil.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Thread the branch tube adapter into the high-pressure oil pump. Do not tighten jam nut
                    at this time. Oil outlet hole must face down.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3900006" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figN11/N11019.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Branch Tube Adaptor Installation Depth Gauge</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, branch tube adaptor must be installed at the correct depth to
                        prevent high-pressure oil leaks.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check branch tube adaptor installed depth by placing
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_185.xml" xrefid="t390000603">Branch Tube Adaptor Installation Depth
                        Gauge
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t390000603"/>
                    on the high-pressure oil pump and aligning gauge holes with branch tube adaptor holes. Install
                    branch tube adaptor at depth that best aligns gauge and adaptor holes.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001211" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj11/J11039.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>High-pressure oil pump inlet and branch tube adapter O-rings</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Branch tube adapter O-ring seal recess</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Branch tube adapter O-ring seal</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure oil pump inlet O-ring seal, #207</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate and install a new O-ring into the branch tube assembly O-ring recess and into
                    the high-pressure oil pump inlet recess.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001221" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figN11/N11022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>High-pressure oil pump and branch tube adaptor</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure oil pump</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Branch tube adaptor</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 30 bolt (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 45 Torx bolt (3)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the high-pressure oil pump and branch tube adapter assembly. Branch tube adaptor
                    oil outlet hole must face down.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install three M8 x 45 bolts securing the high-pressure oil pump to the crankcase and
                    finger tighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the branch tube adaptor and branch tube holes and install two M6 x 30 bolts into
                    the branch tube finger tight.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten three M8 x 45 bolts securing the high-pressure oil pump to the crankcase to
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_373.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">standard torque
                        <xref refid="S300GTG"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001217" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj11/J11049.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Branch tube assembly mounting bolt installation (right)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten two M6 x 40 bolts securing the branch tube assembly to the crankcase to
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_373.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">standard torque
                        <xref refid="S300GTG"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3900006" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figN11/N11017.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Branch tube adaptor and Anti-rotation Handle</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Anti-rotation Handle</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Branch tube adaptor jam nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 30 bolt (2)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, use only Anti-rotation Handle to provide counter-torque for branch
                        tube adaptor while tightening jam nut. Other tools will damage branch tube threads and cause
                        high-pressure oil leaks.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the left M6 x 30 bolt and insert the
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_185.xml" xrefid="t390000603">Anti-rotation Handle</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t390000603"/>
                    into the branch tube assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Provide proper counter-torque on Anti-rotation Handle while tightening branch tube
                    adaptor jam nut with a
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_185.xml" xrefid="t390000603">15/16 inch, 12-point (flare nut) crowfoot
                    </hotlnk>
                    to
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_184.xml" xrefid="E30012B">special torque
                        <xref refid="E30012B"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove Anti-rotation Handle and install left M6 x 30 bolt in the branch tube adaptor.
                    Tighten two M6 x 30 bolts to
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_373.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">standard torque
                        <xref refid="S300GTG"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
